

# Query Param Cleaner (Opera GX Extension)

This browser extension allows you to remove specific query parameters from URLs (like `hilit`, `utm_source`, etc.) and set site-specific blacklists where cleanup should not apply. It also features a popup UI with a dark mode toggle.

## Features

- ✅ Clean URL tracking/query junk
- ✅ Customizable param removal
- ✅ Site blacklist support
- ✅ Dark mode UI
- ✅ Easy popup interface

## Install

1. Clone this repo
2. Go to `opera://extensions`
3. Enable Developer Mode
4. Click “Load unpacked” and select this folder

**Do NOT commit the `.pem` key!**

